TOKYO (AP _ Emperor Hirohito will be remembered for one

But it was his first effective decision as emperor, and his most courageous, that ended the Pacific conflict.
In the days that followed, Hirohito continued his break with tradition.
Still, Hirohito and the imperial system remained important to Japan.
Hirohito was born on April 29, 1901.
The feudal samurai ethic was still strong; when his grandfather died, Gen. Maresuke Nogi, the mentor for the 11-year-old prince, calmly committed ritual suicide to follow the emperor, his master, to the grave.
Hirohito visited England, Scotland, France, Belgium, the Netherlands and Italy, receiving various decorations.
